chapters.title: ON MAY 22, 2012, MUSK AND SPACEX MADE HISTORY WHEN THE COMPANY LAUNCHED ITS FALCON 9 ROCKET INTO SPACE WITH AN UNMANNED CAPSULE.
Musk had not discussed specific deal terms, including price, with any potential financing partners, and his statements about the possible transaction lacked an adequate basis in fact.

LEGAL ADVISORS HAVE WARNED THAT TESLA CHIEF EXECUTIVE ELON MUSK COULD COME UNDER SCRUTINY FROM THE U.S. SECURITY AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION OVER HIS SOCIAL MEDIA ACTIVITY AND PUBLIC STATEMENTS AROUND BITCOIN.

FROM SEPTEMBER 2016 TO JANUARY 2017, WHITE OVERSAW SAFETY FOR THOUSANDS OF WORKERS ON TESLA'S GENERAL ASSEMBLY LINE, IN CHARGE OF RESPONDING TO INJURIES, REVIEWING INJURY RECORDS TEACHING SAFETY CLASSES AND ASSESSING THE FACTORY FOR HAZARDS.
82% of employees agreed Tesla was committed to their health and safety
FROM THE PERIOD OF AUG. 22, 2014-JUNE 21, 2018. THE FOLLOWING OSHA VIOLATIONS WERE FOUND IN THE NATIONAL DATABASE FOR TESLA'S ASSEMBLY PLANT
ONE-THIRD OF ALL VIOLATIONS ACROSS ALL TESLA VENTURES WHICH INCLUDE WAREHOUSES, RETAIL SHOWROOMS, AND TESLA ENERGY WERE ENTERED INTO THE OSHA DATABASE FOR INCIDENTS IN 2018 ALONE.

Ambulances have been called more than 100 times since 2014 for workers experiencing fainting spells, dizziness, seizures, abnormal breathing and chest pains, according to incident reports obtained by the Guardian. Hundreds more were called for injuries and other medical issues.
Tesla Motors founder Martin Eberhard is suing current CEO Elon Musk, accusing Musk of taking control of the company, orchestrating his ouster in 2007...
THE DEFENSIVE STATEMENTS AMID THE CURRENT TRAGEDY AND THE SETTLEMENT OFFER IN LAMBERTS LABOR DISPUTE PROVIDE A WINDOW INTO THE WAY MUSK'S FIRM HAS TRIED TO SILENCE CRITICS – OR PUBLICLY ATTACK THEM.
TESLA HAS REACHED A SETTLEMENT WITH THE ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY OVER HAZARDOUS WASTE VIOLATIONS THAT WERE DISCOVERED AT THE COMPANY'S FACTORY IN FREMONT, CALIFORNIA.
TESLA HAS AGREED TO PAY A $31.000 PENALTY, AND, AS PART OF THE SETTLEMENT, IT WILL ALSO BUY $55,000 WORTH OF EMERGENCY RESPONSE EQUIPMENT FOR THE FREMONT FIRE DEPARTMENT.
